Date: Fri, 24 Jul 1998 13:14:31 -0500
From: Jeffrey Davis <DAVISJP@dhfs.state.wi.us>

Thank you for the query. As of yet the serovar of leptospires in this
outbreak is not known. Results of culture of many specimens of blood and
urine are pending. The precise mechanisms of transmission of leptospires in
this outbreak have not yet been established; however, intensive
investigation is ongoing. The hypotheses offered by your readers [peeing
athletes had already been considered in the investigation, but the testing
of those hypotheses is also pending.
A nice summary of the outbreak and the progress of the investigation to
date is published in the July 24 MMWR and information is accessible through
the CDC website (http://www.cdc.gov) or by calling 1-888-OUTBREAK.
--
Jeffrey P. Davis, MD;
Chief Medical Officer & State Epidemiologist for Communicable Diseases,
Wisconsin Division of Health
e-mail: DAVISJP@dhfs.state.wi.us
